<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 17 at 1:31PM EDT until June 17 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 145 PM EDT
FOR EAST CENTRAL MASON...NORTHWESTERN ROANE AND SOUTHERN JACKSON
COUNTIES...
At 131 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Ripley, moving
southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Ripley, Kenna, Statts Mills, Evans, Given, Kentuck, Fairplain and
Gay.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
